    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5164</citedRange> (Franz)</bibl>, from copy of [Negri]; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#letronne-bourville1848"/>, pp. <citedRange>374-375</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#vattier1850"/>, p. <citedRange>858</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, pp. <citedRange>202-203</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#masson1975"/>, pp. <citedRange>222-223</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>007900</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#thorn2005"/>, p. <citedRange>206</citedRange></bibl> (diplomatic copy from Cassels' notebook); 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cherstich2006"/>, pp. <citedRange>110-111</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>56.2032, 2</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>206</citedRange></bibl> (more complete information from Cassels' notebook);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.20</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64955"><name nymRef="#Μεγώι">Μεγὼι</name>                   
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63972"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἐχέτιμος">Ἐχετίμω</name></persName></persName> 
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#masson1975 #thorn2005">Μεγὼι <note>Thorn's reading from Cassels' archive</note></lem> 
                    <rdg resp="#beschi1970">Μεγὼ</rdg> 
                    <rdg resp="#letronne-bourville1848">Μι<supplied reason="lost">κίπ</supplied>πωι <note>Letronne</note></rdg>
                    <rdg resp="#CIG">Μ<supplied reason="lost">νασ</supplied><unclear>ὼ</unclear> <note>Franz</note></rdg></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Megô fille d'Ekhetimos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Mego daughter of Echetimos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Megò figlia di Echetimos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>ميقو ابنة إخيتيو</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Neither Vattier de Bourville's copy nor Letronne's publication were known to Franz for the publication of <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/>, vol. 
                    <citedRange>III</citedRange></bibl>. There is a mention in the addenda in <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/>, vol. <citedRange>IV</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p>This inscription was not identified by De Cou, although a photograph in the Norton archive, here published for the first time, shows it. So there is no 
                mention of it amongst the corrections to <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/></bibl> appended by <bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/></bibl>.</p>
	       <p>From Cassels' notebook, published by Thorn, it appears that the former had identified the base and insisted that he had the exact reading. 
	       Masson had independantly supposed the right reading.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
